      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>dates</strong> roughly, then add them to a bowl and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Set aside to soak</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634572052554-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634572052554-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634572052554-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634572052554-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634572052554-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> meat-free mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to a bowl with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>soaked chopped dates</strong>, then add them to the bowl and give everything a good mix up until fully combined</p><p>Divide and shape the mixture into 5 meatballs per person, then refrigerate – these are your <strong>meat-free mince meatballs</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1710751749614-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1710751749614-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1710751749614-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1710751749614-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1710751749614-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped pepper</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634572059524-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634572059524-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634572059524-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634572059524-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634572059524-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Lightly cover a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>olive oil</strong> (use kitchen paper to help you spread the oil out evenly!), then add the <strong>meat-free mince meatballs</strong> and put the tray[s] in the oven for 14-15 min or until they're cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1710751757984-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1710751757984-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1710751757984-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1710751757984-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1710751757984-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the meatballs are cooking, add your<strong> bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook over a high heat for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once tender, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634572067450-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634572067450-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634572067450-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634572067450-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634572067450-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the softened pepper with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>harissa paste</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Cook for 2 min or until fragrant, then add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]<strong> </span>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook, covered, for 6 min or until most of the liquid has been absorbed and a sauce has formed – this is your <strong>pepper sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634572071272-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634572071272-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634572071272-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634572071272-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634572071272-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While everything is cooking, pick your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from the stems and discard the stems</p><p>Chop the <strong>mint leaves </strong>finely (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Chop your<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped herbs</strong> to the <strong>drained bulgur wheat</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> herby bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634572075563-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634572075563-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634572075563-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634572075563-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634572075563-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>herby bulgur</strong> topped with a dollop of the<strong> pepper sauce</strong> and your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>sumac </strong>over the<strong> </strong>yoghurt and top with the<strong> meat-free mince meatballs</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved mint leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
